race.description: Hyland Breeders Crown 2YOF Final Mbl Pace (G2)
race.comment: BETTOR BEACH (2) made an ultra impressive debut when she surged home to inflict the first defeat on race rival ARRHYTHMIA in the heats at this circuit and distance. Looks to be loaded with talent and should only be improved by the hitout. A good draw gives her the chance to do it again. It was a shock to see ARRHYTHMIA (4) gunned down in the heats - her first time beaten in eight starts - but she was terrific in coming from the back row and working hard to win the Vicbred Super Series Final at this circuit and distance prior. Expect she'll be peaking again tonight so could find her way back into the winners' stall. ONE MILLIE (3) led for a nice win in the heats and draws to be prominent again. That was her first outing for Emma Stewart and she has upside. WILLOWS GIRL (1) placed from the back row last time and missed by just a head from this barrier when fresh prior. Draws to be competitive. DEGARMEA TEALE (6) may need some luck from this draw but is honest and worth including.
